Kenya Breweries Limited recently launched Baileys Delight, a delicious liquid that blends cream and the luscious taste of African honey to offer a unique taste experience. The product is from the makers of Baileys Original Irish Cream. Speaking during the launch in Nairobi, KBL managing director Jane Karuku the product reinforces the companyâ€™s commitment to breakthrough innovation that will expand consumer experience. Kenya is the second market across Diageo to launch Baileys Delight after Guinness Nigeria. Also present at the launch was EABL head of innovations Joyce Kibe, marketing and innovation Graham Villiers Tuthill and a performance by Kenyan music trio Elani.